node.text:
Riley and I have always made our best efforts to be self-aware, and to reflect on where we stand as ‘influencers’ on these social media platforms, and on this planet. The mark we leave in the mind’s of our viewers, and on the environment is important to us! I think 2020 has made us realise what’s really important, more than ever.. 

So, what do you guys want to see more of, or less of? Now’s your chance ⛵️🐚🎣🔧👨🏻‍🔬🔮🎸🤿🧘 let us know in the comments. And don’t forget to join us in our latest video on YT. x

Track by @pat.devlin_

node.text:
If you missed our latest video, we share some pretty damn exciting news with you guys.  We are overwhelmed with gratitude that two of our favourite marine companies want to be a part of our project 🥳

Essentially the way we are going to move around the world, with sails and electric propulsion, has been taken care of. This is HUGE. We are one step closer to pulling this off. In fact, maybe two or three steps closer 🥺💙🌎 

@doyle_sails , the most reputable sail makers in the world. Riley has been banging on about these guys for over a year now and he’s obsessed with their cableless sails. 😎😎😎

And @oceanvolt , the leaders in the electric propulsion and regeneration industry. We’re so excited to see what the future looks like for them. 😻

We have each and every one of YOU guys to thank for this. We couldn’t have got here without your support, your comments, emails of advice, years and years of watching our videos and sharing them with your friends. Don’t know what else to say other than we feel like the luckiest people on earth!! It looks like we might just get to build our new dream home on the ocean.. 👨‍👩‍👦⛵️✨ #sailinglavagabonde #doylesails #oceanvolt

⁣
Track by @luistrindademusic my golly what a voice! ⁣
⁣
#northatlanticcrossing #gretathunberg

We've had time reflect on this whole Sailing La Vagbonde thing after being on land for a fair few months now. We've decided to spill some beans on how it really went behind the scenes.. in that very first year we met and set sail and made a couple of videos. That faithful first year.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
I often wonder what might have happened or where we might be if we (i) didn't post that video? It was pretty close to never making it off my hard drive at all, for some pretty funny reasons that will be revealed in the video 😂
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
Here's one for you guys - what have you got lurking in the shadows that the world is yet to see? Projects, crafts, talents.. leave me a comment.

And the rest is history..
2014, the year I collided with the man who would become the other half of Sailing La Vagabonde. And the man who would also, unbeknownst to him, become known as 'schmuuki' for 60% of his waking life 🤣🙈
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
Ah well, you win some you loose some hey Riles.
So anyway, how did the adventure start? What were we doing before all this? And how did we manage to make it ‘big’ amongst the bottomless pit of videos that is YouTube?
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
Loads more of your pondering questions are answered in our latest video. One of my favourite, ever. It's up on Patreon now and will hit YT early next week, see you soon x

I’d been meaning to go since Darwin made his way earth side, and somehow never found the time/opportunity. So when we had to go into quarantine and I saw an air bnb with a sauna… that was it 😂 hallelujah. Lol.

node.text: This will be the third week we’ve had away from posting videos (sorry, there won’t be another video tomorrow!). As scary as it has been taking a step back, it’s also been a huge relief. A reminder to myself that WE make the rules, and a silly algorithm doesn’t own us hahaha. We’ve been doing what’s best for our family lately 🧡 still creating content up in north west of Australia (which we cannot wait to share with you… 🐋🚤🦀🌞🏖⛺️) hanging out with friends, completing a running challenge and locking in travel plans for our next big adventure, leaving Australia 29/09 !! Thank YOU, for being here for it all.
